1513192762_16NS3rBdW9zpLmLSQoD8nLTtNVsRF.body:
As I mentioned before, I came up with the idea of KopyKate in retaliation of YouTube copyright takedowns, and Audible Magic. As a YouTuber and content creator myself, I might actually migrate to the site completely one day, and make it my home.
&nbsp;
Audible Magic is simply the most fascistic piece of garbage ever conceived. You could be walking down a street and filming a video .. ... and all of the sudden, comes a car with the speakers on max volume, playing 50 Cent. That alone was enough to get your video flagged at times. Even classical music will get you flagged.
&nbsp;
I like putting background music on some of my videos because, that's the tune that I feel fits the video the best. I'm not much of a composer, and I'd like to be part of internet culture ... but with all the money that you need in order to buy the rights to all the songs, and the rights of all the PNGs, JPGs, that you've used in your video ... ... ... I feel it's become a barrier of entry for more low-income artists and creators.
&nbsp;
The rich get richer as a result of the intellectual property monopoly, which they can sit on for as long as they live, without doing much work .. while somebody who wants to start making funny cat videos at home will probably struggle to get more than 10 views each... that is, if they're lucky not to have their video flagged.
&nbsp;
This is why I propose abolishing copyright, and instead, introducing a Basic Income in order to boost innovation and creative work. Cryptocurrencies could be a good way to pay for such a scheme.
&nbsp;
If we ever did end up replacing media streaming services, then it would be our duty to make money out of it, and redistribute a lot of that wealth. A ZeroNet mega-proxy would be a good way to do it, simply because it's not a good idea to put cryptocurrency miners on zites (they could easily be removed by simply going into the data folder after every update, deleting the Javascript, etc.). The average person is far more likely to use a proxy to stream our content, than download the zeronet client and all the zites on them... which is okay! (My mother uses Play through my proxy.)

